` { doc: "`tail(l)` - return list `l` without the head item. [] causes error."
    export: :suppress }
tail: __TAIL

` { doc: "`nil` - identical to `[]`, the empty list."
    export: :suppress }
nil: []

` { doc: "`if(c, t, f)` - if `c` is `true`, return `t` else `f`."
    export: :suppress }
if: __IF

` { doc: "`cat(a, b)` - explicit catenation, cat(a, b) = a b. Useful in folds etc."
